  levelName: Flipping Coins
  levelDesc: 'A lot of times I was indecisive. I could''ve flipped a coin to make
    a decision, but, being me, I made a program do it for me instead.


    -Merlin'
  levelGoal: Make a program that decides between two options depending on the value
    of a random number.
  startConvo:
  - npcName: Merlin
    showNpc: 1
    npcPos: 82
    npcSprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 3439f81a94f3c0a409645c7a40b9a01a, type: 3}
    lines:
    - I don't look it, but I'm quite indecisive. I had this trinket once, a magic
      8-ball. But I'd rather have something a lot lighter and less obvious.
  passConvo:
  - npcName: Merlin
    showNpc: 1
    npcPos: 82
    npcSprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 9d43eb43e4fc0d84a876fedd867625c4, type: 3}
    lines:
    - The way this is now, it's more like a coin flip than a magic 8-ball, but it
      fulfils a simmilar purpose.
  mainText: "//note: randomNumber is an int with any value from 1 to 20.\n\n_(randomNumber
    > 10_ {\n  _(\"Go^for^it\");\n_\n_ _\n  _(\"My^sources^say^no\");\n}"
